definition.value: The concentration of compound required to kill 50% of a cell population (i.e., 50% inhibitory concentration in a cytotoxicity assay).

50% Tissue Culture Infective Dose (TCID50) is the measure of infectious virus titer. This endpoint dilution assay quantifies the amount of virus required to kill 50% of infected hosts or to produce a cytopathic effect in 50% of inoculated tissue culture cells.
Any result reported as a simple binary assessment, such as 'active/ inactive', 'true/ false', etc.
